            <title>CORTEX_A35</title>
            <!-- Generic description displayed in the first panel of the tooltip -->
            <extract>The Cortex-A35 uses a combination of power reduction&lt;br/&gt;
				 and performance enhancements to deliver efficiency improvements&lt;br/&gt;</extract>
            <!-- Detailed information displayed in the expandable panel when no MCU series has been selected -->
            <help_text>Cortex®-A35 processor marks the beginning of a new family of ultra high efficiency&lt;br/&gt;
			 application processors from ARM&lt;br/&gt;
				The Cortex-A35 processor has several key feature :&lt;br/&gt;
				
           • Scalable and Versatile :Scaling from a single core configuration to up to&lt;br/&gt;
            four cores in a single CPU cluster provides great flexibility for designers.&lt;br/&gt; 
            As it is architecturally compatible with existing&lt;br/&gt;
           Armv8-A processors, the Cortex-A35 can also be connected as a&lt;br/&gt;
           'LITTLE' CPU in a big.LITTLE system.&lt;br/&gt;
                       
           • Power Management :Improving battery life and reducing idle power consumption&lt;br/&gt;
            are critical for next-generation IoT solutions.&lt;br/&gt;
            Cortex- A35 includes advanced power management features to reduce&lt;br/&gt;
            the power budget consumption&lt;br/&gt;
            in always-on applications&lt;br/&gt;
                       
           • 64 -Bit Processing:The Cortex-A35 processor supports the AArch64 execution&lt;br/&gt;
            state, which brings 64-bit processing to embedded applications.&lt;br/&gt;
            Seamless backwards compatibility with Armv7-A software in the&lt;br/&gt;
            AArch32 execution state means that&lt;br/&gt;
            it supports software reuse for cost-effective design.&lt;br/&gt;
            </help_text>
            <!-- Links that will be displayed on the help widgets:
